{"_id":"BloodDrawings","name":"Blood Drawings in the Den","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-torn-brown-red.webp","system":{"description":"Crude drawings on the cave walls of the wolves' den, depicting a mother and daughter holding hands. They are drawn in blood, a haunting testament to Iskra's lost innocence and her desperate longing for the maternal love she was denied. These drawings reveal the tragic humanity still present within the wolf-girl.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Wolves' Lair - Iskra's personal den","importance":"emotional-clue"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"PoisonVial","name":"Elizaveta's Poison","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-purple.webp","system":{"description":"A powerful poison that Elizaveta keeps hidden in the palace. If Iskra is captured, Elizaveta will attempt to use this poison to eliminate her unwanted daughter once and for all. The poison is potent enough to kill even someone with supernatural resilience.","type":"item","uses":{"value":1,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace - Elizaveta's possession","importance":"threat"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"GerardsLetter","name":"Gerard's Letter to the Papacy","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-worn-tan-brown.webp","system":{"description":"A letter written in Lord Gerard Dubois' trembling hand, sent to the Papacy begging for help. The letter reads: 'The beasts that menace the Gévaudan are unnatural, fashioned by something other than God.' This desperate plea brought the Order's Hunters to Durfort.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace","importance":"story-hook"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"IskrasPendant","name":"Iskra's Pendant","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/jewelry/necklace-pendant-moon-silver.webp","system":{"description":"An old earthenware pendant that Iskra once made for her mother as a gift, a memento of a rare moment of happiness. Elizaveta tried to dispose of it by throwing it into the old well at the cemetery, but it can still be found at the bottom of the well. This handmade pendant is crude but touching, showing the innocent love of a child for her mother.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Old Cemetery - Bottom of the well","importance":"crucial-clue"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"IskrasRedCape","name":"Iskra's Red Cape","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/equipment/back/cloak-layered-red.webp","system":{"description":"A threadbare red cape, the last gift from Iskra's mother before she sent her daughter to her supposed death in the forest. Despite its worn condition, Iskra still wears it as both a memory and a symbol of her quest for revenge. The cape is stained with mud and blood from her time living as a wolf.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Worn by Iskra","importance":"iconic-item"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"IskrasWolfMask","name":"Iskra's Wolf Mask","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-wood-tan.webp","system":{"description":"A rudimentary wooden mask carved by Iskra's own hands to hide her face. The mask depicts a wolf's features and serves both to conceal her identity and to express her adopted nature as part of Greskar's wolf pack. The craftsmanship is crude but effective, showing her adaptation to survival in the wild.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Worn by Iskra","importance":"iconic-item"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"BonesPile","name":"Pile of Bones and Corpses","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/commodities/bones/bones-skull-white.webp","system":{"description":"A large cave in the wolves' lair filled with bones and human corpses - the grim remains of the pack's victims. The sight is disturbing and serves as evidence of the wolves' brutality and the danger they pose to Durfort's inhabitants.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Wolves' Lair - Large cave chamber","importance":"atmospheric"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"PatrickDuboisPainting","name":"Portrait of Patrick Dubois","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/misc/portrait-painting-frame.webp","system":{"description":"An enormous painting of Patrick Dubois, Gerard's late father, hanging in the ceremonial hall. The portrait shows a stern and sullen-looking man who seems to judge his son's incompetence from beyond the grave with ill-concealed contempt. Every room in the palace is filled with flattering paintings of Patrick, a constant reminder of Gerard's inadequacy.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace - Ceremonial Hall","importance":"atmospheric"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"SecretPassageway","name":"Secret Passageway Map","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/documents/blueprint-axe.webp","system":{"description":"Knowledge of a secret passageway that connects the large dining room to the inner courtyard of the Dubois Palace. This hidden route was used by Iskra and the wolf pack to launch their surprise attack on the mansion. The passageway may also connect to the underground tunnel leading from the wolves' den to the old well in Durfort's main square.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace / Wolves' Lair","importance":"tactical-information"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"WolfTracks","name":"Wolf Tracks and Child's Footprints","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/misc/paw-print.webp","system":{"description":"In the old cemetery, there are many wolf tracks scattered throughout the grounds. Hidden among them are the prints of two small bare feet, almost certainly belonging to a little girl. These tracks lead deep into the Gévaudan forest, toward the wolves' den. This evidence suggests that a child is somehow involved with the wolf pack.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Old Cemetery","importance":"tracking-clue"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
